						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near the temple of Basavaṇṇa.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This highly damaged and effaced record mentions one Ravideva who, it seems, was a lāḻa <hi rend="italic">sandhivīgrahi.</hi> There is a long description of his family. The beginning and end portions of the record are broken and lost. The purport of it is not clear.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
